values: Hi. I'm Jeremy, and this is MY live journal. So... I am going to write. My dad, today, said to me, and I quote, "Well, you better knock that shit out because that's not a good habit for a young lad like yerself to get in to."  Like yourself? What does THAT mean? Like yourself... like yourself... like I'm not a young lad like everybody else? You'll have to excuse me, today I am drunk. One of those sobering kind of drunks where you really find yourself. I heard my "true voice" today, what I really sound like. And uuuhhhh well... it's okay I suppose but it seems... let me think about this... it seems, uuhhh.... WEAK!!! Yes that is what I think of my own voice... it's WEAK so I have to add some strength to it. Let's see... How how how can I add strength to my voice... with booze? Um... no. I am Jeremy Michael Brown and I would like to be a writer. There's so many words though.... so many words... sooooo many uuhhh  words yeah.. words thats it yeah words you know what I mean? So many words... so many things... so many... um... people... and so many plants. And so many different kinds of... see now I'm thinking too much. Have you ever heard that expression? I think you think too much. Oh wow. I have. I now know what it means to think too much. I been thinking too much my self. What the fuck does my dad know about me? Oh, you better knock that shit out. Oh Oh Oh Oh Oh... DAAAAMMNNNIITTTT  I... I feel so... so much... I feel so... oh oh oh I feel it... I feel... what??!!! fucking say it. Complete a fucking sentence for once in your fucking life and just say it. I feel so... drunk? No no no no I am drunk still it is 8 in the morning. It's one of those drunks where you reallt find yourself you really hear your own voice when your talking and you really... uhhhhhh yup yup there is so much more inside of me than what I just wrote down and I want to find a way to let that out. I wantto find a way to let that out... and what the fuck... what  the   fuck.... aaahhh okay okay I know okay Im back hello Im back and I am going to really find myself yeah yeah cause there is so much to find it has been lots of fun writing in this live journal but now now now now I have to call in sick to work now now now I have to call in sick to work NOW NOW NOW This is my first sick day so I think I'll be okay you know? its my first sick day... ok bye!  Goodbye now, thank you. thank you so much. thank you for listening to me. thank you. thanks. thank you so much. no, thank you. no. no. no. thank you. no no no, thank you. goodbye now! goodbye. BYE! see you later. no I will see YOU later. LIKE YERSELF? what the fuck. okay thank you goodbye.

Hello. I am writing. Uuuh I am writing. Uuuh I am! I am! yeah! I am! look at me write. I'm going to keep on reading and maybe write more in my journal (offline) and maybe I can get my wires uncrossed.
AM I??? =\ Am I retarded? Okay... goodbye.

And noone else is listening. What do I want to say today? Every day I have to reassure myself. I can write. I can paint a picture with the power of my language. English! =) Hablo Espanol? Nope. I speak English, and I speak it WELL!!!!!!! I enjoy writing. Always have. It's something that used to be fun, but I've fallen out of practice. All I have to do is talk. I can talk with a keyboard and I can talk with a pen. I can even talk with my mouth. I just need something to say. I have things to say. Important things. Valuable things. Intelligent things. The things I tell myself surprise, and delight me. Soooooo WHY??? WHY WHY WHY can't I say them out LOOOOUUUD????? =\ Like what? Uuuhh I don't know. Things about love mostly. That's been a big issue for me since I left high school. How can I tell the difference between love and infatuation, when I never give it a TRY???? I want to fight. I'm sick of myself, and so I think I'm going to change. It won't happen over night. It will take time, but it has already begun. So now I find myself wondering what I will become. I want music in my life. I can hear it in my head all the time. Holding it in is getting harder and harder. Sooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo 
Here we go. Here comes a song. Duuuuuuuh. Walking makes me feel good. I walk all the time. One of these days I will walk OUT of my mind. And when that happens I'll be feelin fine. Walking makes me feel good. I walk all the time. Walking eases pain makes me eeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeekkkkeeeinfaoingjapigaipe heetehrhehehehehe nooo hahaha wha   wha  wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha wha heh anyways uuh walking yeah it makes me feel great When I walk I donttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttttt use breaks I walk to pass time and to heal MY mind and it works too Im so lost right now it is no longer funny Im glad today turned out to be sunny cause it started out gray and gee thhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhatts great I dont mind gray days Theyre fine but the sun is so much better when it SHINES! The beatles are a funny band they take me on a tour lost lost I lost I lost loser loser me me yup ok no no NO! heeeelp heeeelp I feel funny... Im going for a walk. OOOH YEAH! Maybe when I come back I'll have something relevant to say. Maybe that's my PROBLEM I always want something important to say. It doesn't have to be so deep don't give it so much MEANING the only subject you need is how the day is SUNNY =) hmmmm ok so what did I say where did I say it to who and when? or... why! No no I've lost it again what have I lost? TTTTTTHHAATTTTTT I dont know. 
Heh.

Outside myself, I see all my problems. I think I've finally figured out how to solve them.
To learn how to talk is my goal. Soon I'll start school, and soon I'll find answers, about things that have happened so far. Why do I stall, how did I fall, where did I lose that fire? And why don't I let myself dance? What happened to having friends? Fun? Anyone? Hmm... I know I'll do better this time around.
Because I will LET myself do better. Now I've found a reason, it doesn't need a rhyme. It just has to give me things to fill my free time (It may not NEED rhyme but I'm still going to try to give it some ;). I want to improve myself, and build up some confidence, so I can learn how to live, and learn to be free, and learn to let myself be me. The human spirit is real, and so is the soul. Now it's time to show that I am filled with both. Now it's time to find that connection between my body and mind. And when I do find it I won't let it go. I'm going to keep the feeling alive forever! I may not find love, but I will find some friends. Because I've had them before. Of this I am SURE. I will find more. And do you know, that alcohol and weed are great. They can be fun, and let you cut loose, and get you in touch with that creative side.  But without reason, or for the wrong reasons, they will only bring pain. (Actually they dull pain, along with other, more important things, and in the end this only leads to misery, and misery is equal to pain.)  Alcohol at least I know is this way, but I'm not so sure about the weed. There's just too many unknowns. I've stopped smoking for now to clear my head, before I go back to school. In a month or two I'll try it again just to see how it really makes me feel. I do know one thing. Excess is BAD. You know what I'm saying? Too much of anything will hurt. Well maybe not ANYthing. There are better ways to get high. Music is one way I've enjoyed in the past, and I will enjoy it again. YO YO soooooooooo I'm gonna go. It's been fun talking to myself in a healthy way. :)  Goodbye (said the AOL guy.)

It was for a painting he's going to make. It looked really cool. It was a rough sketch in water colors. CRAZY CRAZY WE'RE ALL OF US GOING CRAZY and that makes all of us the same :)Because if everyone is crazy then noone is insane. Sanity is for posers. Hmmmm... burn!! =) Heh. I thought that was kind of strange. Im in there all the time anyways letting the girls take my money... They make me leave big tits... I mean tips! Hahaha... it's evil! But I don't mind. :) I love this website. It's like talking to myself, but other people can read it too! I don't go as fast here though... Maybe I should give it a try because I can type pretty fast when I want to. But sometimes I just can't think fast enough to keep up with my typing speed. Maybe I smoke too much pot? I know it was in there somewhere.. a good song... its like having something on the tip of your tongue. Something to say but you just can't quite say it. Can't quite see what it is. Can't quite get a grip... Just can't shake those hips! hahaha I like to dance, and I don't care if I can't. :) I want to have fun again. What happened to me??!!! :( Talk is cheap. If you want to do something than do it! So I got this job and its really lame cause all I do is kill time all day and I wish I could be doing something better but I've got bills to pay =\ I'm tired of killing time, and I want to get laid :) Really really bad actually... It's pretty much all I think about. Heh. Walking around downtown there were beautiful ladies everywhere, walking in gangs.  I passed this group of 4 really hot ones and on a radio in a store the song Girls Just Want To Have Fun was played. I started singing along but changing the words making my own song. It went something along the lines of I want to have fun with you blah blah blah blah (Only it was musical so it wasn't stupid and it wasn't those exact words). It was really cool... I was singing it for a while and I got a lot of words hammered out. It gave me hope :) Let me show you how much fun I can be! That was one of the lines. And there was a bunch of other stuff that rhymed with that. Well it didnt all rhyme with that... songs that rhyme the same sound all the time suck... its too much like rap. Some rap is cool though. It's definitely it's own form of art. I don't think anyone can argue with that. It's just not a very good one IMHO. :)

Work is cool, I work with a crazy mexican dude. Drumming is still fun. I've been  drawing stuff recently. Not much, just some weird crazy shapes and things with a pen, but I think it looks artistic. I got a new hackey-sack. It's hand-made, and it's made of suede. It's a freestyle dirtbag with a well balanced 8 panel design! I purchased it from the Canadian Footbag Alliance, in Canada (from their webpage.) And as always, I'm ready and waiting for another LIVE SHOW!!!! The Misfits concert rocked. I forgot to bring some drumsticks for Robo to sign, but I did get them to sign my shirt and my Heritage coffee card. The mosh pit was intense. It was the first time I've ever been in a real mosh pit. I need more. Shows around here suck because the only ones who mosh with me are little high-schoolers and I just knock them all down. Hahahaha!!!!! But not at this concert! I was covered in bruises after the show, and my eye had a small purple mark around it that almost looked like a black eye. Someone elbowed me in the face. After the concert I went stumbling around down town and people were asking if I was drunk, but I wasn't. The music did it to me! And the moshing. It gets me so high.

I ordered a cheeseburger pizza from dominoes and it was the worst pizza I've ever eaten. The chick that answered the phone and took my order sounded cute though. I think she was in to me, too. Hah. She asked if I wanted it delivered or if I would pick it up. I should have picked it up. Oh well. Things have pretty much gone completely crazy over the past month thats all I can say for now. Bye.

Wow I actually sound like a normal person. I feel like one too. I've come to the conclusion that my parents suck and I want to get as far away from them as possible. Its lame hanging around my parents house all the time why do I do it? Thats gotta change. A job would help. A job would help a lot. But working sucks. It doesnt have to though. Working at Capital Service could be fun I'll give them a call tomorrow. It gets me pumped up just thinking about working there! Hahaha... because its a gas station... and I would be pumping gas... for money. Thats it. Thats all Id have to do. Run out and pump gas and hang out and bullshit with the other employees. Smoke a bowl during lunch. And get a check every week, or maybe two. Fuck yeah. Sounds good to me.

God I have no confidence I've spent the rest of this day trying to convince myself that I really did mean what I wrote earlier. But I can feel that doubt creeping back. Oh Jeremy you dont have what it takes. Youre ugly and stupid and youll never get what you want. You can't sing you have a terrible voice. WTF. Doubt sucks. Why do people think like that? I'm done. It's up to me to change the way I think and what I do in my life. Fucking grow up. I'm going to find a job, damnit. I was singing along to less than jake in the car on my way home from keiths place (watched a sharks tale, ate some papa murphys thin crust pepperoni and took some hits off the bong, good times) and I think I actually sounded good. I cant be sure though. I've seen that show Motormouth on VH1 and I know how people can be somewhat disillusioned when it comes to there singing skills. (Somewhat??) But I had the volume turned down real low and I was singing kinda loud and what I heard didn't sound to bad. And I know I have the ears for it because I've been trained musically, starting in the 5th grade. I might not have been the most astute person ever to play an instrument but I know I'm not tone deaf. And now its time for Daily Affirmations with Stewart Smalley. Because Im good enough, Im smart enough, and dog gonnit, people like me. :P

I've only felt this way one other time. And that was on drugs. Drugs never last, but I'm sober now.
I'm already feeling scared again though. Just thinking about grabbing that mic and wailing out a song... 
Aaahh so now we get to the real problem. I can't see myself. I look in the mirror and see nothing there.
There was one time that I looked into a mirror and saw a real person. He was cool too. He was someone I want to be.
He looked like some guy from a movie. Is that me? Do I look like that all the time or only when I'm HIIIIIIIGH?
I was so baked... and I followed that up with 4 shots in a row, and a 5th shot a few minutes later.
I stood in the bathroom for 10 minutes staring at myself and thinking, laughing, and bouncing around.
I never cried though... really... crying is stupid. At one point I was just screaming to myself with my forehead pressed up against the mirror. The world was bending at that point and I think I heard a snap.
But anyways, I know that if I could just get to the point where I can look in a mirror and see that person all of the time I know that I can turn into something real...

How do I do that? I'd like it to be that way when I'm sober but maybe I need to start drinking all of the time.

I gave the loot to Keith and sent him out to the bar to find some weed for me. He came back with 2 bags! The guy handed him an extra sack on accident, and we smoked it all. Oh and my dad gave me some money to go to the store and buy some ice cream for him. I kept the change from that and used it to put gas in my truck.

Thats all folks! The beast is going back into his cage now. :P

... but not long enough, apparently. I can't think of anything to write about. I guess I don't have anything to write about because all I've been doing is playing World of Warcraft. I could write about that but I won't. OH YEAH!!!! I went up to Eaglecrest for the first time in three years a week from yesterday! It was a lot of fun. I decided to go skiing, because my brother skis, and I'm not as good on a snowboard as he is on skis, so he would have left me behind. I'm a much better skiier than him, though. It was fun. By my third run I was back up on Ptarmigan. It's amazing how quickly I picked it up again. Heh, I got to ride in one of those ski patrol sleds... I was going down Motherload, but that looked to easy so I went off into the trees to the side. There's a much steeper, and better, run right there. I was doing great until I hit some deep powder. I tried to turn in it and my ski got caught in the snow. My foot was twisted incredibly fast and I heard a loud pop. I fell over after that. I crawled over to the side of the hill and took my boot off. I couldn't walk on my foot. It burned when I tried to stand. Luckily some passersby saw me and went to get the ski patrol. The sled ride was fun. Those things go fast! The ski patrol lady was nice. She went and got me some fries. Then I went to the ER, and got it x-rayed. Only a sprain. They gave me a splint and sent me home. All I got was a prescription for ibuprofen. =\ Oh well. There's another $1k bucks I owe the hospital. Hahahaha. Good thing I can pay in $1 dollar increments. Anyways, that was a week ago. I haven't been able to walk all week and I've just been playing computer. My foot is starting to heal and I can almost walk like normal. I think it's time I got away from my room. So, who's going to give me something to do?
I'm currently playing Shining Force 2 and it is (like the title says) the best game ever. I just beat the Hobgoblin cave and now I'm headed to Mt. Volcano!

BECAUSE TODAY SUCKS 
                                                   - Happy New Year -
Come on! Juneau! Please! I know we can do better! =\ Ok maybe we can't. Fuck it. I'm staying home and listening to CDs like everybody else. And fuck the police, too.

It's really my mom's computer, but I did kick it's ass! It had a virus that kept messing with Internet Explorer. Nortons couldn't get rid of it, but I did! Thats about the only excitement I've seen so far today, other than playing with the dog... He likes all this snow. Oh, there was a funny skit on Mad TV today. It featured Ms. Swan on an airplane, and she wouldn't quit kicking the guys seat, or stop pressing the call button. She said the button was broken, but then she pressed the button right in front of the flight attendant, and she still said it was broken. Oh, and also when the food cart passed by she wanted the vegetarian meal with just a little bit of bacon. That made me laugh, because last week I ordered a vegetarian pizza from Bullwinkles and told them to put hamburger on it. Coincedence? I think not! Something's going on here... Television has become a reflection of my life. So who's seat have I been kicking? And what does that button do that I keep pressing? Just kidding. There would be some cool shit on TV if that happened. Mars Attacks! was on today, that was cool. Tom Jones (AKA Mr. Vegas) kicked ass in that movie. And Danny Devito got the flesh melted from his bones. AAHH CRAP! The stupid plow guy just  blocked my truck with a massive pile of snow!! I'm mad now. This is bullshit. I can't write anymore.

Hmm I just read yesterdays post. That was a fun Christmas. I didn't go to sleep after I wrote that though. I actually stayed up till about 4:30 in the morning. =) I went to Fred Meyers today and spent my 50 dollar gift card on 3 CDs. Less Than Jake - Anthem, The Ramones - Road To Ruin, and Iron Maiden - Live After Death. My brother bought the Dawn Of The Dead Directors Cut. Cool movie, and since it's the director's version it's unrated and has added scenes! Other than that it's been a boring day filled with television. =\

Went on a walk tonight. That was fun. The moon is full and bright, but it's tiny. It was bright out tonight. Listened to a punk mix I made. It's pretty good. Has songs that I like from a bunch of different bands. Doesn't feel like 10:43... Uhh.. concert coming up thats gonna rock... Had a chance to play my drums today. That was a lot of fun. My brother thinks I'm getting better. Oh boy! Went over to the relatives house for Christmas. Always a lot of fun, and a lot of drinking hahaha I had 5 beers there and 5 mixed drinks at home today. Rum and Root Beer. It's good stuff. Rum straight sucks, though. I can't drink it. Has to be mixed for me. Whiskey! Thats something I can drink straight, as long as it's good whiskey. And by good whiskey I mean Crown Royale. I have a cold, and I hate it. Playing drums is fun, and I am looking forward to this next concert, because I haven't been to a live show since Halloween, and I'm great at writing huge run-on sentences, because it's fun, and I just can't seem to stop myself, or use any conjuntions besides and or because, but I guess I am using other ones, so maybe I should just end this sentence, because it's becoming way to long and soon I might have to use a semi-colon or maybe even a full colon. There it's over! Hahaha. That was fun. I'm going to bed. I know it's only 10:52pm but dangit I don't care anymore. The show last night was great!  I started at my brother Keith's place at 7 oclock.  He had to take a shower so I listened to some Bob Marley while drinking a beer.  After Keith got out of the shower we finished off his bottle of Bacardi and headed out.  We stopped by Robert's  house on the way to the show.  I wanted to get up there but they had a Hookah so I stayed.  It's a good thing too because somebody showed up with a bottle of crown and I got to take a few shots.  We saw some idiot tape himself to a lightpole outside.  It was cool except the kid didn't stay up there long enough.  He started ripping the tape off before his buddies were even finished putting him up there!  Saw some drunk guy yelling at a "hippy queer" in the Imperial.  Hippies suck.  After a few rounds of cards it was time to get up to that show.  So we said our goodbyes and ran up there.  Some highschool kid told us it wasn't worth it to go up there because there was a line and you had to pay 3 bucks.  Highschoolers suck.  We got there while What Remains was playing.  That was cool, they rocked hard but nobody was moshing.  After What Remains played Keith and I went to get some beer.  Walking down to the store we ran into Cole, the singer for Contra Public.  He invited us up to their studio!  I was sitting in Contra Public's studio getting wasted with their singer, and I got to play the drums.  It was fun.  I listened to a few songs that are going into the new CD that they're producing right now!  Did I mention I played Contra Public's drums?  While Cole was playing some acoustic guitar!  I want to be in a band!!  After that we stopped by Roberto's house again to drop off the rest of the beer.  When we got back up to the VFW hall Old Goat was playing.  FUCK YEAH!! Old Goat man, they're awesome, I was moshing.  I kicked Keith's ass too he sucks at moshing.  There were some guys in costumes moshing with us but everyone else just stood back or sat at the tables.  Hippy queers =\  Heh, anyways we moshed to Old Goat for what seemed like hours, and eventually the big guy in an awesome goat/demon halloween mask grabbed a knife and told his cowboy partner to hold a pumpkin over a garbage can while he started stabbing away.  He went insane too, must have stabbed that pumpkin a thousand times, he carved a face.  About half way through the carving the cowboy dropped the pumpkin.  After watching the big guy struggling to keep carving while holding up the pumpkin himself I ran in and held it for him, that was fun, Keith says he saw blood on the dude's hands!  That is hardcore.  Oh, and between the second visit to Robert's and Old Goat's performance I talked to Dave, from What Remains, for a while.  They're going to be getting a bass player and a new guitarist soon, which is good, because no bass sucks, no matter how much you rock!  The whole night was great, shows like this are what Juneau has been missing.  We need more crazy people like me here to get out there and get moshing though! =D
